introduction.p:
Suppose that you were asked to find the value of \fe{\fd{h}}{2} where \fe{h}{x}=\fe{f}{x}\fe{g}{x}.  The first thing you would need to do is find a formula for \fe{\fd{h}}{x}.  You would then replace x with 2, substitute the appropriate function and derivative values, and simplify.  This is illustrated below.
                \fe{\fd{h}}{x}&=\lzoo{x}{\fe{f}{x}}\fe{g}{x}+\fe{f}{x}\lzoo{x}{\fe{g}{x}} 
                &=\fe{\fd{f}}{x}\fe{g}{x}+\fe{f}{x}\fe{\fd{g}}{x} 
                \fe{\fd{h}}{2}&=\fe{\fd{f}}{2}\fe{g}{2}+\fe{f}{2}\fe{\fd{g}}{2} 
                &=7(11)+4(37) 
                &=225 
                Following the process outlined in this example, find each of the following.
